Entry.Definition: Automatically derived freeform textual reference to a key sound in the data set

Entry.Name: Computed Key Data
Entry.Definition: Automatically derived freeform textual reference to a key piece of data or program in the data set

Entry.Name: Computed Textual Description
Entry.Definition: Automated textual characterization of the data set.

Entry.Name: Automated Stratum
Entry.Definition: Automatically derived descriptive stratum of the archival content analysis of the content

Entry.Name: Computed Stratum Kind
Entry.Definition: Automatically derived descriptive stratum of the content (e.g., background, action, sound nature)

Entry.Name: Computed Technical Comments and Descriptions
Entry.Definition: Technical comments or descriptions relating to system

Entry.Name: Computed Object Comments and Descriptions
Entry.Definition: Comments or descriptions relating to objects

Entry.Name: Computed Object Kind
Entry.Definition: Specifies the kind of object (e.g., a plugin)

Entry.Name: Computed Object Kind
Entry.Definition: Specifies the kind of object (e.g., a plugin)

Entry.Name: Version Number String
Entry.Definition: Specifies the string version number of the code

Entry.Name: Version Number String
Entry.Definition: Specifies the string version number of the code

Entry.Name: Version Number
Entry.Definition: Specifies the version number of the code

Entry.Name: Object Identification Confidence
Entry.Definition: Percentage confidence that an identified object in the current field of view is the same object identified, detected or tracked in another or previous view. This is an indication that the track of a moving object has been maintained.
Entry.Notes: Format is PPPD where PPP is the percentage confidence from 0 (zero) to 100 and D is tenths of a percent.

Entry.Name: Object Horizontal Average Dimension
Entry.Definition: Average number of horizontal pixels when a bounding rectangle is placed around an object in the frame or field of view.
Entry.Notes: Sides of the bounding rectangle are parallel to the sides of the image frame.

Entry.Name: Object Vertical Average Dimension
Entry.Definition: Average number of vertical pixels or lines when a bounding rectangle is placed around an object in the frame or field of view.
Entry.Notes: Sides of the bounding rectangle are parallel to the sides of the image frame.

Entry.Name: Object Area Dimension
Entry.Definition: Count of the number of pixels comprising an object in the frame or field of view.

Entry.Name: Derived Summary Information
Entry.Definition: Summary Information derived from other Metadata

Entry.Name: WAVE Summary
Entry.Definition: Summary info according to WAVE Chunk format

Entry.Name: AIFC Summary
Entry.Definition: Summary info according to AIFC Chunk format

Entry.Name: TIFF Summary
Entry.Definition: Summary info according to TIFF format

Entry.Name: Device Comments and Descriptions
Entry.Definition: Technical comments or descriptions relating to devices

Entry.Name: Device Usage Description
Entry.Definition: Freeform textual description of the function or use of the device in the production of a specific content item

Entry.Name: Device Usage Description
Entry.Definition: Freeform textual description of the function or use of the device in the production of a specific content item

Entry.Name: PARAMETRIC
Entry.Definition: Class 4 is reserved for parametric and configuration metadata.

Entry.Name: Video and Image Essence Characteristics
Entry.Definition: All parametric aspects of the video/image essence

Entry.Name: Fundamental Image Characteristics
Entry.Definition: Fundamental characteristics of the image

Entry.Name: Aspect Ratios
Entry.Definition: Specifies the horizontal to vertical aspect ratio of the image.

Entry.Name: Presentation Aspect Ratio
Entry.Definition: Specifies the horizontal to vertical aspect ratio of the whole image as it is to be presented to avoid geometric distortion and hence including any black edges.

Entry.Name: Capture Aspect Ratio
Entry.Definition: Specifies the horizontal to vertical aspect ratio of the image captured at the sensor - hence after the (possibly anamorphic) lens.

Entry.Name: Viewport Aspect Ratio
Entry.Definition: Specifies the horizontal to vertical aspect ratio of the image viewport - ie. The desired shot as it is framed for capture and thus the aspect ratio at which the image must be viewed to avoid geometric distortion. May also therefore be a sub-selection of a larger image, possibly of a different aspect ratio.

Entry.Name: Horizontal Action Safe Percentage
Entry.Definition: Specifies the percentage of the image which lies outside the horizontal safe area for action: expressed as the ratio of one side as a percentage of the total width of the scan.

Entry.Name: Vertical Action Safe Percentage
Entry.Definition: Specifies the percentage of the image which lies outside the vertical safe area for action: expressed as the ratio of one side as a percentage of the total height of the scan.

Entry.Name: Horizontal Graphics Safe Percentage
Entry.Definition: Specifies the percentage of the image which lies outside the horizontal safe area for graphics: expressed as the ratio of one side as a percentage of the total width of the scan.

Entry.Name: Vertical Graphics Safe Percentage
Entry.Definition: Specifies the percentage of the image which lies outside the vertical safe area for graphics: expressed as the ratio of one side as a percentage of the total height of the scan.

Entry.Name: Perceived Display Format Name
Entry.Definition: Colloquial description of the image when viewed in its intended aspect ratio on a display of another aspect ratio - e.g. pillarbox, letterbox, mixed etc.

Entry.Name: Perceived Display Format Code
Entry.Definition: A code for the colloquial description of the image when viewed in its intended aspect ratio on a display of another aspect ratio (e.g., a code for pillarbox, letterbox, mixed)

Entry.Name: AFD and Bar Data
Entry.Definition: The Active Format Description and Bar Data is a concatenated series of codes, flags, and values that signal the active image area being used for program content. The content and structure of the payload information value shall be coded as described in SMPTE 2016-3.

Entry.Name: Pan Scan Information
Entry.Definition: The Pan-Scan information is a concatenated series of codes, flags, and values that describe a variable image viewport and the output aspect ratio.

Entry.Name: Image Source Characteristics
Entry.Definition: Fundamental characteristics of the image source

Entry.Name: Opto-Electronic Formulation
Entry.Definition: Fundamental opto-elecronic transfer etc characteristics

Entry.Name: Transfer Characteristics
Entry.Definition: Specifies the non-linear relationship between linear scene light levels and amplitude-compressed video signal levels.

Entry.Name: Capture Gamma Equation
Entry.Definition: Specifies the non-linear relationship between linear scene light levels and amplitude-compressed video signal levels at signal origination.

Entry.Name: Capture Gamma Equation
Entry.Definition: Specifies the non-linear relationship between linear scene light levels and amplitude-compressed video signal levels at signal origination.

Entry.Name: Transfer Characteristic
Entry.Definition: Specifies the non-linear relationship between linear scene light levels and amplitude-compressed video signal levels at signal origination.

Entry.Name: Luma Equation
Entry.Definition: Specifies the equation used to derive luma and chroma from gamma-corrected RGB signals

Entry.Name: Colorimetry Code
Entry.Definition: The fundamental color coding that relates the scene CIE tri-stimulus values (X, Y, Z) to the linear video levels (R, G, B).

Entry.Name: Coding Equations
Entry.Definition: The fundamental color coding that relates the scene CIE tri-stimulus values (X, Y, Z) to the linear video levels (R, G, B).

Entry.Name: Signal Form Code
Entry.Definition: Code specifies the component sequence for the video pixel matrix (eg RGB, YUV etc).

Entry.Name: Video Color Kind
Entry.Definition: The type of color of the video (B/W, color, etc)

Entry.Name: Color Primaries
Entry.Definition: The set of color primaries used

Entry.Name: Color Primaries
Entry.Definition: The set of color primaries used

Entry.Name: Presentation Gamma Equation
Entry.Definition: Specifies the non-linear relationship between the input video signal levels and the resulting displayed light levels on the display.

Entry.Name: Presentation Gamma Equation
Entry.Definition: Specifies the non-linear relationship between the input video signal levels and the resulting displayed light levels on the display.

Entry.Name: Sensor Parameters
Entry.Definition: Settings and adjustments for image sensors

Entry.Name: Sensor Mode
Entry.Definition: The mode setting of the sensor as a text string

Entry.Name: Video and Image Scanning Parameters
Entry.Definition: Fundemental scanning and sequencing information

Entry.Name: Temporal Parameters
Entry.Definition: Time dependant sequencing and scanning information

Entry.Name: Color Field Code
Entry.Definition: Identifies the color field of the source video field for video derived from composite sources.

Entry.Name: Field Rate
Entry.Definition: Specifies the field rate of the video scanning system.

Entry.Name: Frame Rate
Entry.Definition: The rate that video images are captured, expressed in frames per second.

Entry.Name: Capture Frame Rate
Entry.Definition: The rate that video images are captured expressed in frames per second (for example, 50:1, 60000:1001).

Entry.Name: Frame Layout
Entry.Definition: Specifies frame layout (interlaced, single frame, full frame, etc.)
Entry.Notes: AAF names this type "LayoutType"

Entry.Name: Sampling Structure Code
Entry.Definition: A code that specifies the analogue or digital sampling structure for the video scanning system. Eg Progressive

Entry.Name: Field Dominance
Entry.Definition: Specifies whether the first frame of picture is field 1 or field 2

Entry.Name: Picture Display Rate
Entry.Definition: The rate at which pictures must be displayed in order to achieve the intended editorial effect, expressed in pictures per second.

Entry.Name: Vertical Parameters
Entry.Definition: Vertical scanning information

Entry.Name: Total Lines per Frame
Entry.Definition: Specifies the number of lines in a total frame in the video scanning system.

Entry.Name: Active Lines per Frame
Entry.Definition: Specifies the total number of lines (rows) in the active portion of a frame in the video pixel matrix.

Entry.Name: Leading Lines
Entry.Definition: Specifies the number of leading lines in the processed image to be blanked before display

Entry.Name: Trailing Lines
Entry.Definition: Specifies the number of trailing lines in the processed image to be blanked before display

Entry.Name: Video Line Map
Entry.Definition: Specifies the line numbers of the two top lines of the active picture

Entry.Name: Display F2 Offset
Entry.Definition: Topness Adjustment for displayed picture

Entry.Name: Stored F2 Offset
Entry.Definition: Topness Adjustment for stored picture

Entry.Name: Active Format Descriptor
Entry.Definition: Specifies the intended framing of the content within the displayed image (4:3 in 16:9 etc.)

Entry.Name: Line Number
Entry.Definition: Specifies the video line number to which a block of essence data corresponds

Entry.Name: Alternative Center Cuts
Entry.Definition: Specifies the alternate aspect ratio subset(s) of the active area, containing all of the critical action and centered on the active area.

Entry.Name: Horizontal Parameters
Entry.Definition: Horizontal scanning information

Entry.Name: Analog Video Coding Characteristics
Entry.Definition: Information about the analogue coding of the essence

Entry.Name: Analog Video System Name
Entry.Definition: PAL, NTSC etc

Entry.Name: Video Signal
Entry.Definition: PAL, NTSC etc

Entry.Name: Video Scanning Characteristics
Entry.Definition: Information about the scanning of the essence

Entry.Name: Scanning Direction
Entry.Definition: Enumerated Scanning Direction
Entry.Notes: AAF names this type "OrientationType"

Entry.Name: Digital Video and Image Coding Parameters
Entry.Definition: Information about the essence digital coding

Entry.Name: Digital Video and Image Sampling Parameters
Entry.Definition: Inflormation about the digital sampling

Entry.Name: Luminance Sample Rate
Entry.Definition: The luminance sample rate

Entry.Name: Active Samples per Line
Entry.Definition: Total number of samples (columns) in the active portion of a line in the video pixel matrix.

Entry.Name: Total Samples per Line
Entry.Definition: Specifies the number of samples in a total line in the video pixel matrix.

Entry.Name: Sampling Hierarchy Code
Entry.Definition: A code that specifies the component sampling hierarchy for the video pixel matrix.

Entry.Name: Horizontal Sub-sampling
Entry.Definition: Specifies ratio of luminance subsampling to chrominance subsampling in horizontal direction

Entry.Name: Color Siting
Entry.Definition: Specifies how to compute subsampled chrominance values
Entry.Notes: AAF names this type"ColorSitingType"

Entry.Name: Sampled Height
Entry.Definition: Specifies the integer height of the sampled image in pixels

Entry.Name: Sampled Width
Entry.Definition: Specifies the integer width of the sampled image in pixels

Entry.Name: Sampled X-Offset
Entry.Definition: Specifies the X offset of the sampled image relative to the stored image in pixels

Entry.Name: Sampled Y-Offset
Entry.Definition: Specifies the Y offset of the sampled image relative to the stored image in pixels

Entry.Name: Display Height
Entry.Definition: Specifies the height of the presented image relative to the sampled image in pixels

Entry.Name: Display Width
Entry.Definition: Specifies the width of the presented image in pixels

Entry.Name: Display X-Offset
Entry.Definition: Specifies the X offset of the presented image relative to the sampled image in pixels

Entry.Name: Display Y-Offset
Entry.Definition: Specifies the Y offset of the presented image relative to the sampled image in pixels

Entry.Name: Filtering Code
Entry.Definition: Specifies the spectral filtering that has been applied to the digital samples of the video signal.

Entry.Name: Vertical Sub-sampling
Entry.Definition: Specifies ratio of luminance subsampling to chrominance subsampling in vertical direction

Entry.Name: Video Average Bit Rate
Entry.Definition: The Average bit rate in bits per second

Entry.Name: Video Fixed Bit Rate
Entry.Definition: Fixed = TRUE, variable = FALSE

Entry.Name: Active Height
Entry.Definition: Specifies the height of the Active Area Rectangle

Entry.Name: Active Width
Entry.Definition: Specifies the width of the Active Area Rectangle

Entry.Name: Active X Offset
Entry.Definition: Specifies the horizontal offset of the Active Area Rectangle from the left side of the Display Rectangle

Entry.Name: Active Y Offset
Entry.Definition: Specifies the vertical offset of the Active Area Rectangle from the upper side of the Display Rectangle.

Entry.Name: Digital Video and Image Storage Parameters
Entry.Definition: Information about image storage parameters.

Entry.Name: Stored Height
Entry.Definition: Specifies the integer height of the stored image in pixels

Entry.Name: Stored Width
Entry.Definition: Specifies the integer width of the stored image in pixels

Entry.Name: VBI Line Count
Entry.Definition: Number of VBI lines stored in a Data Element

Entry.Name: Stored VBI Line Number
Entry.Definition: The line number of this stored VBI line according to SMPTE 377M-2004 E.1.5

Entry.Name: VBI Wrapping Type
Entry.Definition: Enumerated wrapping type of the VBI data payload

Entry.Name: VBI Payload Sample Count
Entry.Definition: A count of the number of samples stored in the payload byte array

Entry.Name: VBI Payload Byte Array
Entry.Definition: An array of Uint8 samples containing the coded VBI data

Entry.Name: ANC Packet Count
Entry.Definition: Number of ANC packets stored in a Data Element

Entry.Name: Stored ANC Line Number
Entry.Definition: The line number of this stored ANC packet according to SMPTE 377M-2004 E.1.5

Entry.Name: ANC Wrapping Type
Entry.Definition: Enumerated wrapping type of the VBI data payload

Entry.Name: ANC Payload Sample Count
Entry.Definition: A count of the number of samples stored in the payload byte array

Entry.Name: ANC Payload Byte Array
Entry.Definition: An array of Uint8 samples containing the coded ANC data

Entry.Name: Digital Quantization and Level Parameters
Entry.Definition: Inflormation about the digital quantisation and levels

Entry.Name: Bits per Pixel
Entry.Definition: The maximum number of significant bits for the value in each band of each pixel without compression.

Entry.Name: Bits per Pixel
Entry.Definition: The maximum number of significant bits for the value in each band of each pixel without compression.

Entry.Name: Rounding Method Code
Entry.Definition: Specifies the rounding method that has been applied to the digital samples of the video signal.

Entry.Name: Black Reference Level
Entry.Definition: Specifies digital luminance associated with black

Entry.Name: White Reference Level
Entry.Definition: Specifies digital luminance associated with white

Entry.Name: Color Range Levels
Entry.Definition: Specifies the range of the color levels.

Entry.Name: Pixel Layout
Entry.Definition: Specifies pixel quantisation and order as a data structure.
Entry.Notes: Annex E.2.46

Entry.Name: Alpha Sample Depth
Entry.Definition: Specifies the number of bits in the alpha signal.

Entry.Name: Palette
Entry.Definition: Specifies, as a single string, the fixed length values of each color in the palette used.
Entry.Notes: Annex E.2.46

Entry.Name: Palette Layout
Entry.Definition: Specifies pixel quantisation and order in the palette as a data structure.
Entry.Notes: Annex E.2.46

Entry.Name: Component Depth
Entry.Definition: Specifies the number of active bits per sample (e.g. 8, 10, 16 etc)

Entry.Name: Component Maximum Ref
Entry.Definition: Maximum value for RGB components e.g. 235 or 940 (8 or 10 bits)

Entry.Name: Component Minimum Ref
Entry.Definition: Minumum value for RGB components e.g. 16 or 64 (8 or 10-bits)

Entry.Name: Alpha Maximum Ref
Entry.Definition: Maximum value for alpha component e.g. 235 or 940 (8 or 10 bits)

Entry.Name: Alpha Minimum Ref
Entry.Definition: Minumum value for alpha components e.g. 16 or 64 (8 or 10-bits)

Entry.Name: VBI Payload Sample Coding
Entry.Definition: Enumerated sample coding of VBI payload

Entry.Name: ANC Payload Sample Coding
Entry.Definition: Enumerated sample coding of ANC payload

Entry.Name: Digital Video and Image Signal Type Identifiers
Entry.Definition: Identifiers of the specific standard to which a video signal conforms

Entry.Name: Video Payload Identifier
Entry.Definition: SMPTE 352M-2001 Video Payload Identifier

Entry.Name: Video Payload Identifier 2002
Entry.Definition: SMPTE 352M-2002 Video Payload Identifier
Entry.Notes: Note 2002 revision date

Entry.Name: Digital Video and Image Compression Parameters
Entry.Definition: Information about the digital video compression scheme used (MPEG, DV etc)

Entry.Name: Video Coding Scheme ID
Entry.Definition: Specifies the Compression scheme used

Entry.Name: MPEG Coding Parameters
Entry.Definition: Information about MPEG video coding

Entry.Name: MPEG-2 Coding Parameters
Entry.Definition: Information about MPEG video coding

Entry.Name: Field Frame Type Code
Entry.Definition: Identifies the field or frame type of the source video image for video derived from compressed sources. Eg, I B or P

Entry.Name: Single Sequence Flag
Entry.Definition: TRUE if the essence consists of a single MPEG sequence. False if there are a number of sequences. This flag implies that the sequence header information is not varying in the essence stream.

Entry.Name: Constant B Picture Flag
Entry.Definition: TRUE if the number of B frames is always constant

Entry.Name: Coded Content Scanning Kind
Entry.Definition: The type of scanning used in MPEG video coded content as a code (e.g., 0=Unknown, 1=Progressive, 2=Interlaced, 3=Mixed)

Entry.Name: Low Delay Indicator
Entry.Definition: TRUE if low delay mode was used in the sequence

Entry.Name: Closed GOP Indicator
Entry.Definition: TRUE if closed_gop is set in all GOP Headers, per 13818-1 IBP descriptor

Entry.Name: Identical GOP Indicator
Entry.Definition: TRUE if every GOP in the sequence is constructed the same, per 13818-1 IBP descriptor

Entry.Name: Maximum GOP Size
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum occurring spacing between I frames, per 13818-1 IBP descriptor. A value of 0 or the absence of this property implies no limit to the maximum GOP

Entry.Name: Maximum B Picture Count
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum number of B pictures between P or I frames, equivalent to 13818-2 annex D (M-1)

Entry.Name: Profile And Level
Entry.Definition: Specifies the MPEG-2 video profile and level. The value is taken directly from the profile_and_level_indication in the MPEG-2 sequence header extension. For main profile @ main level, the value is 0x48. For 4:2:2 profile @ main level, the value is 0x85

Entry.Name: Bit Rate
Entry.Definition: Maximum bit rate of MPEG video elementary stream in bit/s as defined in ISO-13818-2 bit_rate property

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Coding Parameters
Entry.Definition: Describes MPEG-4 Visual coding parameters.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual VOP Coding Type
Entry.Definition: Identifies whether a VOP is an intra-coded VOP (I), predictive-coded VOP (P), bidirectionally predictive-coded (B) or sprite coded (S).

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Single Sequence
Entry.Definition: TRUE if the essence consists of a single MPEG sequence. False if there are a number of sequences. This flag implies that the sequence header information is not varying in the essence stream.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Constant B-VOPs
Entry.Definition: TRUE if the number of B-VOPs is always constant.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Coded Content Type
Entry.Definition: 0= "Unknown" 1= "Progressive" 2= "Interlaced" 3= "Mixed" An enumerated value which tells if the underlying content which was MPEG coded was of a known type.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Low Delay
Entry.Definition: TRUE if the VOL contains no B-VOPs.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Closed GOV
Entry.Definition: TRUE if closed_gov is set in all GOV headers. An example is defined in closed_gop_flag of ISO/IEC 13818-1 IBP descriptor.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Identical GOV
Entry.Definition: TRUE if every GOV in the sequence is constructed the same. An example is defined in identical_gop_flag of ISO/IEC 13818-1 IBP descriptor.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Max GOV
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum occurring spacing between I frames. An example is defined in max_gop_length of ISO/IEC 13818-1 IBP descriptor. A value of 0 or the absence of this property implies no limit to the maximum GOV or the maximum GOV is unknown.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual B-VOP Count
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum number of B-VOPs between P or I-VOPs.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Profile And Level
Entry.Definition: Specifies the MPEG-4 Part 2 video profile and level. The meaning of the bits is given in Table G.1 of ISO/IEC 14496-2.

Entry.Name: MPEG-4 Visual Bit Rate
Entry.Definition: Maximum bit rate of MPEG-4 Part.2 video ES in bit/s.An example is defined in ISO/IEC 14496-2 bit_rate property.

Entry.Name: JPEG 2000 Coding Parameters
Entry.Definition: Information about JPEG 2000 picture coding

Entry.Name: Rsiz
Entry.Definition: An enumerated value that defines the decoder capabilities. Values are defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5 Table A-10. Other values may be defined in amendments to ISO/IEC 15444-1 or in related international standards documents.

Entry.Name: Xsiz
Entry.Definition: Width of the reference grid, as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1.

Entry.Name: Ysiz
Entry.Definition: Height of the reference grid, as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1.

Entry.Name: XOsiz
Entry.Definition: Horizontal offset from the origin of the reference grid to the left side of the image area, as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1.

Entry.Name: YOsiz
Entry.Definition: Vertical offset from the origin of the reference grid to the top side of the image area, as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1.

Entry.Name: XTsiz
Entry.Definition: Width of one reference tile with respect to the reference grid, as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1.

Entry.Name: YTsiz
Entry.Definition: Height of one reference tile with respect to the reference grid, as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1.

Entry.Name: XTOsiz
Entry.Definition: Horizontal offset from the origin of the reference grid to the left side of the first tile, as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1.

Entry.Name: YTOsiz
Entry.Definition: Vertical offset from the origin of the reference grid to the top side of the first tile, as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1.

Entry.Name: Csiz
Entry.Definition: The number of components in the picture as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1. If this Sub Descriptor is referenced by the CDCI Descriptor, the order and kind of components shall be as defined by the Essence Container UL in the MXF File Descriptor. If this Sub Descriptor is referenced by the RGBA Descriptor, the order and kind of components shall be as defined by the Pixel Layout property of the RGBA Descriptor.

Entry.Name: Picture Component Sizing
Entry.Definition: Array of picture components where each component comprises 3 bytes named Ssizi, XRSizi, YRSizi (as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1 Annex A.5.1). The array of 3-byte groups is preceded by the array header comprising a 4-byte value of the number of components followed by a 4-byte value of '3'.

Entry.Name: Coding Style Default
Entry.Definition: Default coding style for all components. Use this value only if static for all pictures in the Essence Container.The data format is as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1, Annex A.6.1 and comprises the sequence of Scod (1 byte per table A-12), SGcod (4 bytes per table A.12) and Spcod (5 bytes plus 0 or more precinct size bytes per table A.12)

Entry.Name: Quantization Default
Entry.Definition: Default quantization style for all components. Use this value only if static for all pictures in the Essence Container.The data format is as defined in ISO/IEC 15444-1, Annex A.6.4 and comprises the sequence of Sqcd (1 byte per table A.27) followed by one or more Sqcdi bytes (for the ith sub-band in the defined order per table A.27).

Entry.Name: J2C Layout
Entry.Definition: The nature and order of the image components in the compressed domain as carried in the J2C codestream.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Picture Essence Descriptors
Entry.Definition: Defines the VC-1 Picture Essence Descriptor Set.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Initialization Metadata
Entry.Definition: Encodes the metadata defined in SMPTE 421 annex J for Simple and Main Profile bitstreams.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Single Sequence
Entry.Definition: TRUE is the essence consists of a single VC-a sequence. FALSE if there are a number of sequences. This flag implies that the sequence header information is not varying in the essence stream.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Coded Content Type
Entry.Definition: An enumerated value that tells if the underlying content was of a known VC-1 type. Enumerations are 0="Unknown", 1="Progressive, 2= "Interlaced," "3=Mixed."

Entry.Name: VC-1 Identical GOP
Entry.Definition: A boolean value, using TRUE to indicate that all GOPs in the sequence are constructed the same.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Maximum GOP
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum occuring spacing between I-frames. A value of '0", or the absence of this property implies no limit to the maximum GOP.

Entry.Name: VC-1 B Picture Count
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum number of B pictures between P or I frames. BI pictures count as B pictures and skipped pictures count as P pictures.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Average Bit Rate
Entry.Definition: Specifies the average bit rate of VC-1 video elementary streams in bits-per-second.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Maximum Bit Rate
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum bit rate of VC-1 video elementary streams in bits-per-second.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Profile
Entry.Definition: Specifies the VC-1 profile. Coded as per SMPTE 421M, Annex J.1.2.

Entry.Name: VC-1 Level
Entry.Definition: Specifies the VC-1 video level. This is coded as per SMPTE 421M, Annex J.I.2.

Entry.Name: TIFF Coding Parameters
Entry.Definition: Information about TIFF picture coding

Entry.Name: TIFF Byte Order
Entry.Definition: Byte order of the essence data. Shall be 'MM' = Big endian or 'II' = Little endian

Entry.Name: TIFF Bits Per Sample Array
Entry.Definition: Array of the number of bits allocated for each component in an uncompressed pixel, where n = Number of components per pixel. Shall be encoded as defined for BitsPerSample in ISO 12234-2

Entry.Name: TIFF Compression Kind
Entry.Definition: Compression scheme used to store the image data. Shall be 1 = No compression or 7 = Lossless Huffman JPEG compression. Shall be encoded as defined for Compression in ISO 12234-2

Entry.Name: TIFF Photometric Interpretation Kind
Entry.Definition: Color space and order of image data components. Shall be 32803 = Color Filter Array or 34892 = Linear Raw. Shall be encoded as defined for PhotometricInterpretation in ISO 12234-2

Entry.Name: TIFF Orientation
Entry.Definition: Orientation of the camera relative to the scene, when the image was captured. Shall be encoded as defined for Orientation in ISO 12234-2.

Entry.Name: TIFF Samples Per Pixel
Entry.Definition: Number of components (n) per pixel. Shall be 1 for Photometric Interpretation = 32083 or 3 for PhotometricInterpretation = 34892. Shall be encoded as defined for SamplesPerPixel in ISO 12234-2

Entry.Name: TIFF Light Source Kind
Entry.Definition: Predominant light source (scene illuminant) present when the image was captured, or its color temperature. Shall be encoded as defined for LightSource in ISO 12234-2

Entry.Name: AVC Parameters
Entry.Definition: Parameters about AVC Picture Coding

Entry.Name: AVC Constant B Picture Flag
Entry.Definition: TRUE if the number of B Pictures is always constant.

Entry.Name: AVC Coded Content Kind
Entry.Definition: Enumerated value specifying Picture type and Coding type.

Entry.Name: AVC Closed GOP Indicator
Entry.Definition: TRUE if all GOPs are started with IDR Picture.

Entry.Name: AVC Identical GOP Indicator
Entry.Definition: TRUE if every GOP in the sequence has the same number of pictures and the same types of pictures in the same order.

Entry.Name: AVC Maximum GOP Size
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum occurring spacing between I Pictures. A value of 0 or the absence of this property indicates either there is no limit to the maximum GOP or the maximum GOP is unknown.

Entry.Name: AVC Maximum B-Picture Count
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum number of B Pictures between P or I Pictures.

Entry.Name: AVC Profile
Entry.Definition: Specifies the AVC video profile.

Entry.Name: AVC Maximum Bit Rate
Entry.Definition: Maximum bit rate of the AVC stream in bit/s

Entry.Name: AVC Profile Constraint
Entry.Definition: Specifies the AVC video profile constraint flags.

Entry.Name: AVC Level
Entry.Definition: Specifies the AVC level.

Entry.Name: AVC Decoding Delay
Entry.Definition: Specifies the delay required for decoded pictures in number of access units.

Entry.Name: AVC Maximum Ref Frames
Entry.Definition: Specifies the maximum number of reference frames.

Entry.Name: AVC Sequence Parameter Set Flag
Entry.Definition: Specifies the location and the constancy of sequence parameter sets

Entry.Name: Platform Roll Angle
Entry.Definition: Roll angle of platform expressed in degrees. The Roll of an airborne platform is rotation about its longitudinal (front-to-back) axis; wings level is zero degrees, positive (negative) angles describe a platform orientation with the right wing down(up). Range of values is -180 to +180 degrees

Entry.Name: Platform Pitch Angle
Entry.Definition: Pitch angle of platform expressed in degrees.The Pitch of an airborne platform describes the angle of its longitudinal (front-to-back) axis makes with the horizontal (i.e., equi-potential gravitational surface); positive (negative) angles describe a nose up (down) orientation. Range of values is -90 to +90 degrees.

Entry.Name: Platform Heading Angle
Entry.Definition: Heading angle of platform expressed in degrees. The Heading of an airborne platform is the angle from True North of its longitudinal axis projected onto the horizontal plane. Range of values is 000 to almost 360 degrees; North is 000, East is 090; South is 180, and West is 270.

Entry.Definition: A set of AUIDs where each AUID identifies a "file format" "Block" to which the MXF file conforms. A "file format" "Block" is a "Block" (a Rules Framework Component) that is usually at (or close to) the root of a Rules-based Specification.

Entry.Name: Audio Object Interaction
Entry.Definition: Set of parameters for limiting the amount of interaction of an object.

Entry.Name: On Off Interact
Entry.Definition: Set to true to allow interaction.

Entry.Name: Gain Interact
Entry.Definition: Set to true to allow gain interaction.

Entry.Name: Position Interact
Entry.Definition: Set to true to allow position interaction.

Entry.Name: Gain Interact Range Sets
Entry.Definition: Set the range of gain values allowed for interaction.

Entry.Name: Position Interaction Range Sets
Entry.Definition: Set the range of position values allowed for interaction.

Entry.Name: Gain Interaction Range
Entry.Definition: To specify the supported range of gain interaction.

Entry.Name: Gain Interaction Range Value
Entry.Definition: Value defining the range of gain.

Entry.Name: Gain Interaction Range Bound
Entry.Definition: Set attribute to "min" to provide minimum gain factor of possible user gain interaction (gainMin = gain (or 1.0 if not defined) * gainInteractionRangeMin) Set attribute to "max" to provide maximum gain factor of possible user gain interaction gainMax = gain (or 1.0 if not defined) * gainInteractionRangeMin)

Entry.Name: Position Interaction Range
Entry.Definition: To specify the supportes range of supported position interaction.

Entry.Name: Position Interaction Range Value
Entry.Definition: Value defnining the range of position.

Entry.Name: Position Interaction Range Coordinate
Entry.Definition: Set attribute to either "X", "Y", "Z", "azimuth", "elevation" or "distance" to set which axis requires limiting.

Entry.Name: Position Interaction Range Bound
Entry.Definition: Set attribute to either "min" or "max" to set whether the axis needs a minimum or maximum range for positioning limiting.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Position
Entry.Definition: A set of user defined parameters to define a block location in space.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Position Value

Entry.Name: Audio Block Position Bound
Entry.Definition: Set to "min" or "max" to set the bound of the position.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Position Edge Lock
Entry.Definition: Set to "left", "right", "top" or "bottom" to indicate which edge of the screen to lock the position to.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Divergence
Entry.Definition: Sets the divergence of an object where 0.0 means all sound in the direction of the object and 1.0 means all sound from the virtual objects placed at an angle set by the azimuthRange attribute value.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Divergence Value
Entry.Definition: The value of divergence.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Divergence Azimuth Range
Entry.Definition: Set the azimuth angle from the actual object's position to the two virtual positions each side of it.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Exclusion
Entry.Definition: Allows 3D zones to be exluded from rendering. So any speakers that exist within the excluded zone will not be used.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Sets
Entry.Definition: Specifies the corner points of a cuboid in the 3D space that will be excluded from rendering. Multiple zone elements can be used to specify more complex exclusion shapes.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone
Entry.Definition: Specifies the corner points of a cuboid in the 3D space that will be excluded from rendering. Multiple zone elements can be used to specify more complex exclusion shapes.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Value
Entry.Definition: The definition of a zone.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Min X
Entry.Definition: Min X

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Max X
Entry.Definition: Max X

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Min Y
Entry.Definition: Min Y

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Max Y
Entry.Definition: Max Y

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Min Z
Entry.Definition: Min Z

Entry.Name: Audio Block Zone Max Z
Entry.Definition: Max Z

Entry.Name: Audio Block Jump Position
Entry.Definition: If set to 1 the position will be interpolated over a period set by the attribute interpolationLength. If set to 0 then interpolation will take the entire length of the block. An interpolationLength value of zero will mean the object jumps without interpolation.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Jump Position Flag
Entry.Definition: Jump position flag value.

Entry.Name: Audio Block Jump Position Interpolation Length
Entry.Definition: The interpolation length in seconds.

Entry.Name: APP Format
Entry.Definition: The technical code describing the method or recording of this element. E.g. 'LTO', 'D3' (Infax table T_RECORDING, item tech_code)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Programme Title
Entry.Definition: Indicates the series the programme is related to. E.g. 'OLD GREY WHISTLE TEST' (Infax table T_PROGRAMME, item series_title)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Episode Title
Entry.Definition: The title of this programme. E.g. 'PICK OF THE YEAR'(Infax table T_PROGRAMME, item core_title)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Transmission Date
Entry.Definition: Earliest transmission date E.g. 1978-01-05 (Infax table T_PROGRAMME, item fst_aptx_date)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Magazine Prefix
Entry.Definition: Programmes are identified by a programme number and optionally a magazine prefix, which consists of a letter, ranging from A to Z. E.g. 'A'(Infax table T_PROGRAMME, item mag_prefix)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Programme Number
Entry.Definition: A number, which in conjunction with the magazine prefix, uniquely identifies a programme. It never changes and stays with the programme throughout its life.E.g. LNF2073N (Infax table T_PROGRAMME, item prog_num)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Spool Status
Entry.Definition: This is a code to describe the recording status of spool items.E.g. 'M'(Infax table T_RECORDING, item rec_status
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Stock Date
Entry.Definition: The date on which this element was recorded onto the spool item. E.g. 2008-04-17 (Infax table T_RECORDING, item rec_date)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Spool Descriptor
Entry.Definition: A free format text containing a technical description of the recording. E.g. 'PROGRAMME (DUB OF 005123) (Infax table T_RECORDING, item rec_vt_desc)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Memo
Entry.Definition: The catalogue description of the recording. (Infax table T_RECORDING, item rec_cat_desc)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Duration
Entry.Definition: The amount of material used. This is recorded as duration in number of seconds. E.g. 4145 (Infax table T_RECORDING, item rec_duration)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Spool Number
Entry.Definition: The numeric component of a spool number. The number and prefix form a spool-number which is usually issued when the material is created. The spool number equates to a gap in the short term store. The number on the spool identifies the last current number for the spool. E.g. 'DA 005123'(Infax table T_SPOOL, item spl_prefix and spl_num)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Accession Number
Entry.Definition: The accession number identifies a number given to an item being added to the library's long term store system. This number equates to a space on a storage shelf and is therefore a reusable storage identifier.E.g. 'DA 018820'(Infax table T_SPOOL, item acc_prefix and acc_num)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Catalogue Detail
Entry.Definition: A code which allows the user to retrieve catalogue entries by a category. It is a subcatalogue within the catalogue.E.g. 'LONPROG' (Infax table T_CAT_ITEM, item cat_recall)
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Production Code
Entry.Definition: The production code assigned to the programme. E.g. 70
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Item Number
Entry.Definition: Index of the item on the videotape containing multiple items E.g. 1
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Red Flash
Entry.Definition: The value of the red flash analysis, scaled by a factor of 1000.
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Spatial Pattern
Entry.Definition: The value of the spatial analysis, scaled by a factor of 1000.
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Luminance Flash
Entry.Definition: The value of the luminance flash analysis, scaled by a factor of 1000
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Extended Failure
Entry.Definition: The extended warning failure flag
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP VTR Error Code
Entry.Definition: Error code reported by the VTR
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP Strength
Entry.Definition: Normalised Digibeta dropout strength
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 233 Archive Preservation File Format: DigiBeta System

Entry.Name: APP Timecode Type
Entry.Definition: Flags which timecode types are associated with this event
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 233 Archive Preservation File Format: DigiBeta System

Entry.Name: APP VTR Error Count
Entry.Definition: Total number of VTR replay errors
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Name: APP PSE Failure Count
Entry.Definition: Total number of PSE analysis failures
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 167 D3 Preservation File Format

Entry.Definition: Total number of DigiBeta dropouts detected

Entry.Name: APP Timecode Break Count
Entry.Definition: Total number of Timecode break events
Entry.DefiningDocument: BBC Research White Paper WHP 233 Archive Preservation File Format: DigiBeta System

Entry.Name: Production Number
Entry.Definition: A unique identifier / code for the programme (i.e. a unique identifier for this version of the episode).
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Synopsis
Entry.Definition: A brief descriptive summary of the programme.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Originator
Entry.Definition: The name of the person or organisation responsible for creating the programme.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Copyright Year
Entry.Definition: The full year in which one of the following occurred or will occur: completion of the production of the programme; delivery of the completed file to the Broadcaster; transmission of the delivered programme.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Other Identifier
Entry.Definition: Another unique identifier / code for the content.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Other Identifier type
Entry.Definition: The kind of identifier / code used for "Other Identifier".
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Genre
Entry.Definition: A single style or category describing the whole programme.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Distributor
Entry.Definition: The name of the person or organisation responsible for supplying the programme to the Broadcaster.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Picture Ratio
Entry.Definition: The ratio of the display width to the display height of the smallest rectangle that completely contains (throughout the duration of the entire programme) the region of the video frame used for "programme content" (where "programme content" includes all pictures, captions, etc but excludes any black bars).
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: 3D
Entry.Definition: A flag to indicate whether the file contains video intended for stereoscopic rendition.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: 3D Type
Entry.Definition: A code to identify the kind of stereoscopic video contained in the file.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Product Placement
Entry.Definition: A flag to indicate whether the programme contains "product placement".
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: PSE Pass
Entry.Definition: A code to indicate: whether the entire programme passed a flash and pattern test for compliance with Photosensitive Epilepsy (PSE) guidelines; or that such a test has not been carried out.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: PSE Manufacturer
Entry.Definition: The name of the product used to perform the test for compliance with PSE guidelines.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: PSE Version
Entry.Definition: The version of the algorithm / product module used to perform the test for compliance with PSE guidelines.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Video Comments
Entry.Definition: A description of the subjective quality of the video in the programme including notes on any global characteristics or video treatments.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Secondary Audio Language
Entry.Definition: A code to identify the main language used on secondary audio channels.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Tertiary Audio Language
Entry.Definition: A code to identify the main language used on tertiary audio channels.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Audio Loudness Standard
Entry.Definition: A code to identify a relevant audio loudness recommendation or standard.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Audio Comments
Entry.Definition: A description of the subjective quality of the audio in the programme including notes on any global characteristics or audio treatments.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Line Up Start
Entry.Definition: The value of the Position in the MXF Material Package at which the line-up test signals begin.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Ident Clock Start
Entry.Definition: The value of the Position in the MXF Material Package at which the initial "ident" or countdown clock begins.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Total Number Of Parts
Entry.Definition: The count of parts / segments in the file.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Total Programme Duration
Entry.Definition: The sum of the durations of all the parts / segments in the entire programme.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Audio Description Present
Entry.Definition: A flag to indicate whether the programme contains audio description for the visually impaired.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Audio Description Type
Entry.Definition: A code to identify the format of the audio description.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Open Captions Present
Entry.Definition: A flag to indicate whether the programme contains visible (in-vision) subtitling information.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Open Captions Type
Entry.Definition: A code to identify the editorial description of the open captions.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Open Captions Language
Entry.Definition: A code to identify the main language used in the open captions.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Signing Present
Entry.Definition: A code to indicate: whether the programme contains visible (in-vision) signing along with the rest of the programme content; or that the programme contains only visible (in-vision) signing.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Sign Language
Entry.Definition: A code to identify the main language and / or format of the visible (in-vision) signing contained in the programme.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Completion Date
Entry.Definition: The date on which the programme file was completed ready for delivery to the Broadcaster.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Textless Elements Exist

Entry.Name: Contact Email

Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: Contact Telephone No.
Entry.Definition: The telephone number for the person or organisation responsible for supplying the programme file to the Broadcaster.
Entry.DefiningDocument: AMWA Application Specification AS-11 MXF Program Contribution

Entry.Name: AS_07_Elements
Entry.Definition: AS-07 Archiving and Preservation Format Elements

Entry.Name: AS_07_DMS_Elements
Entry.Definition: AS-07 Archiving and Preservation Format Descriptive Metadata Elements

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_ShimName
Entry.Definition: Controlled vocabulary string value indicating the AS-07 Shim Name, e.g., Derived-from-video-serial-interface

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_Identifiers
Entry.Definition: Unordered list of strong references to all AS_07_DMS_Identifier sets. At least one AS_07_DMS_Identifier Objects set is required with the IdentifierRole = Main. Other AS_07_DMSIdentifierObjects sets are optional.

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_ResponsibleOrganizationName
Entry.Definition: The main name for the entity responsible for the creation, maintenance, preservation of this digital item

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_ResponsibleOrganizationCode
Entry.Definition: A familiar abbreviation of entity name.

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_NatureOfOrganization
Entry.Definition: The nature of an organization (e.g., limited company, government department, etc.)

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_WorkingTitle
Entry.Definition: Free text: Best known or working title of the production or production component

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_SecondaryTitle
Entry.Definition: Free text Secondary title of the production or production component

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_PictureFormat
Entry.Definition: The signal standard (frame resolution and aspect ratio) of the encoded file.

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_IntendedAFD
Entry.Definition: String value indicating the intended display format for the program, per SMPTE 2016-1 table 1 a3 a2 a1 a0 with optional informative appended text e.g. 1001 Pillarbox, 0100 Letterbox, 1000 FullHD

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_Captions
Entry.Definition: Y/N value to indicate if captions are present in the encoded file

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_AudioTrackPrimaryLanguage
Entry.Definition: The primary language in audio track by codes as defined by RFC5646. Use only when language is known.

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_AudioTrackSecondaryLanguage
Entry.Definition: The secondary language in audio track by codes as defined by RFC5646. If multiple secondary language are present the RFC tags in white space separated list. Use only when secondary languages are present and language is known

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_AudioTrackLayout
Entry.Definition: Appropriate values in AS-07 Appendix E

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_AudioTrackLayoutComment
Entry.Definition: Free text comment to augment AS_07_Core_DMS_AudioTrackLayout. This is for track tagging information and is not to be used for descriptive essays. Robust descriptive data can be held in Supplemental Metadata in GSPs.

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_Devices
Entry.Definition: strong references to all AS_07_Core_DMS_Device objects used in this file

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_DeviceType
Entry.Definition: the kind of device used to capture or create the content (as either a commonly known name or as a locally defined name; e.g., Radio-camera)

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_DeviceManufacturer
Entry.Definition: The manufacturer or maker of the device

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_DeviceModel
Entry.Definition: Identifies the device model used in capturing or generating the essence.

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_DeviceSerialNumber
Entry.Definition: Alphanumeric serial number identifying the individual device

Entry.Name: AS_07_Core_DMS_DeviceUsageDescription
Entry.Definition: Free text description of the function or use of the device in the production of a specific content item

Entry.Name: AS_07_DMS_IdentifierValue
Entry.Definition: Identifier Value

Entry.Name: AS_07_DMS_IdentifierRole
Entry.Definition: Controlled vocabulary string value identifying the role of identifier

Entry.Name: AS_07_DMS_IdentifierType
Entry.Definition: Controlled vocabulary string value identifying the type of identifier

Entry.Name: AS_07_DMS_IdentifierComment
Entry.Definition: Free text comment pertaining to the additional identifier

Entry.Name: AS_07_GSP_DMS_Identifiers
Entry.Definition: Unordered list of strong references to all AS_07_DMS_Identifier sets. At least one AS_07_DMS_Identifier Objects set is required with the IdentifierRole = Main. Other AS_07_DMSIdentifierObjects sets are optional.

Entry.Name: AS_07_GSP_DMS_MIMEMediaType
Entry.Definition: Text string that defines the data type of the text. A value shall be selected from the values listed at the following web site. http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/text/

Entry.Name: AS_07_GSP_DMS_DataDescription
Entry.Definition: Controlled vocabulary string identifying the role of the data within the AS-07 file

Entry.Name: AS_07_GSP_DMS_Note
Entry.Definition: Free text note pertaining to the GSP data payload.

Entry.Name: AS_07_GSP_Elements
Entry.Definition: AS-07 Archiving and Preservation Format Generic Stream Partition Elements

Entry.Name: AS_07_GSP_TD_DMS_PrimaryRFC5646LanguageCode
Entry.Definition: Identifies the primary language in Timed Text by codes defined by RFC5646

Entry.Name: AS_07_GSP_TD_DMS_SecondaryRFC5646LanguageCode
Entry.Definition: Identifies the secondary language in Timed Text by codes defined by RFC5646. If multiple secondary languages are present, the RFC tags in white space separated list. Use only when secondary languages are present and language is known.

Entry.Name: AS_07_Segmentation_Elements
Entry.Definition: AS-07 Archiving and Preservation Format SegmentationElements

Entry.Name: AS_07_Segmentation_DMS_PartNumber
Entry.Definition: Identifier for the part number. Combined with AS_07_Segmentation_DMS_PartTotal, these metadata items represent part numbers of the form 1 of 3, 2 of 3, 3 of 3 with AS_07_Segmentation_DMS_PartNumber being the first integer.

Entry.Name: AS_07_Segmentation_DMS_PartTotal
Entry.Definition: The total number of parts in the program. Combined with AS_07_Segmentation_DMS_PartNumber, these metadata items represent part numbers of the form 1 of 3, 2 of 3, 3 of 3 with AS_07_Segmentation_DMS_PartTotal being the second integer.

Entry.Name: AS_07_DateTimeSymbol
Entry.Definition: Symbol that specifies the timecode, values listed in the SMPTE Labels Register as defined by SMPTE ST 400

Entry.Name: AS_07_DateTimeEssenceTrackID
Entry.Definition: Link to (value of) the Track ID of the audio track where the timecode data is stored in a Top Level Source Package

Entry.Name: AS_07_DateTimeChannelID
Entry.Definition: The numerical channel identifier within the essence, if applicable.

Entry.Name: AS_07_DateTimeDescription
Entry.Definition: Additional optional text description of the timecode origin or role or details
